skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "2d55d82b-cacd-4e88-8c0e-cc5c709f6666", "value": "This collection is for CAAL specific concept collections"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "8968e705-c8a3-4a73-8e9d-6416121909a7", "value": "CAAL"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "64509b2c-0b42-4690-b3c1-4c7c1ac510e1", "value": "Any activity, undertaken by professional archaeologists or experienced amateurs, that has a physical impact, actual or potential, upon the archaeological resource, substituting the physical resource with recorded information."}

{"id": "5da920c4-f55d-4291-a983-1620b0fdeb48", "value": "Intervention into the archaeological resource intended to gather information about past ecologies and economies, formation processes, and to retrieve material for scientific dating purposes."}
{"id": "70dd92a2-08d8-4860-a9e3-03377bb8045b", "value": "Any activities, that have a physical impact upon the archaeological resource where the purpose is not primarily archaeological research."}
{"id": "d1f07121-0394-46ea-86bc-c05f5cd9de12", "value": "Starts c. ?10th millennia BCE, until farming cultures develop in the second half of the 5th millennium BCE. c. 14,000-6,500 BCE."}

{"id": "a444834d-5e97-44fa-b47c-0e6a66b2046e", "value": "Sarmatians flourished from c. 5th century BCE to the 4th century CE. Originating in the central parts of the Eurasian Steppe, the Sarmatians started migrating westward around the 4th and 3rd centuries BCE."}
{"id": "cad9be6f-932a-44e3-b908-71f2f26fb406", "value": "Preferred term in Kazakhstan for early Hellenistic. c. 331 BCE to 312 BCE"}
{"id": "0fb1e486-2ae3-43f6-8bf4-ecf0b4c4d2c0", "value": "Uyghur Khaganate (or Uyghur Empire or Uighur Khaganate), 744\u2013840 CE."}
{"id": "c10924b9-f80e-4b4d-8032-cc68ebee03f8", "value": "A tribal confederation of nomadic peoples who inhabited the eastern Eurasian Steppe from the 3rd century BCE to the late 1st century CE."}
{"id": "e95a8caf-0b9a-4871-ab90-d8e3b61f9644", "value": "Maximum date range. c. 331 BCE to 312 BCE"}

{"id": "10733276-578c-466e-ae73-f7cc609adb30", "value": "The systematic collection of samples from a defined study area analysed for phosphate content. Elevated concentrations of phosphate are a generalised signature of human activity."}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "1ac42beb-d501-438d-acf2-da9271fe17fa", "value": "Mayemir stage of Early Iron Age of Altay and Eastern Kazakhstan"}
skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "be4c9a35-3a91-4726-a894-d448ad32c61f", "value": "end of the 9th \u2013 2nd-3rd quarter of the 6th century BCE"}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "77bbdbac-a03d-4f57-98c4-07ed0cc560d1", "value": "Kulazhorgin stage of Early Iron Age of Altay and Eastern Kazakhstan"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "820f5394-9b49-4fa3-8497-e891a43f9f07", "value": "An underwater technique that records bathymetric (depth) data by generating point depths in a line directly beneath the transducer mounted on a vessel as it progresses along the acquisition line."}

{"id": "83017b21-6bb2-442d-871b-2472bd677f93", "value": "Underwater investigation of the seabed, using side-looking sonar device that emits fan shaped acoustic pulses down toward the seafloor. The intensity of the acoustic reflections from the sea floor are recorded as an image of the seabed."}

{"id": "721d2230-7af4-4383-b20c-4d000c8a5fdd", "value": "An underwater technique used to create 3D terrain models and to record objects on the seabed through the comparative analysis of reflections from high frequency sound waves emitted in multiple beams allowing large swathes of the seabed to be surveyed."}

{"id": "863748bd-0504-4950-9c06-effb51ab4190", "value": "Active sonar systems are based on the behaviour of sound waves in water; acoustic energy is transmitted and the time for the returning echo is measured to allow submerged seabed features to be mapped. Use specific type where known."}

{"id": "861fc747-02f4-4876-a6d0-b967c54a2e81", "value": "A maritime investigation that records depth data which can be used to map submerged topography utilising echo sounders which emit a short acoustic pulse. Depth is calculated by measuring the time taken for the pulse to be reflected back to the transducer."}

{"id": "aff4bdd0-7e90-4a85-ba82-389bc274ce56", "value": "Used to identify and measure various sediment layers that exist below the seabed. A sound source emits a signal vertically downwards and a receiver monitors the return signal that has been reflected off the seafloor and sub seabed sediment layers."}
{"id": "26b3e532-7114-49eb-80a5-53a9c4518adb", "value": "Describes the confidence of the accuracy of the coordinates given"}
{"id": "068c0dec-ffcc-4d33-9544-da616a83f16c", "value": "Very confident that the coordinates are accurate"}
{"id": "213d5888-7f87-42b3-bd9f-569a5e26e4cf", "value": "Fairly confident in the accuracy of the coordinates"}

{"id": "1ba48577-8eb7-42d2-b26b-bf7a378efe0f", "value": "The systematic study of ground surfaces and collection of visible archaeological material. Fieldwalking can be carried out as line-walking, grid collection and transect or quadrant sampling. Any material recovered is logged and stored by sample unit."}
{"id": "72329478-3a5d-4962-9c82-566fdc18ae9f", "value": "The unsystematic study of ground surfaces and collection of visible archaeological material."}

{"id": "5c5c12d1-64d5-4a37-9e02-71643c4b399a", "value": "7th c BCE - 8th century CE. Early Iron Age: 7th-6th \u2013 4th-3rd/2nd centuries BCE), Parthian-Sarmat period: 4th-3rd/2nd centuries BCE \u2013 3rd-4th centuries CE, Sasanian and Early-Medieval (Pre-Islamic) period 3rd-4th \u2013 7th-8th centuries CE. "}

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "4be6f5bb-935e-4fa0-8f6d-9c927e442710", "value": "Sedentary-agricultural cultures of the South-Eastern Aral Sea region"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "0d3385a9-ec48-4a89-9dbd-a8cde68a3126", "value": " from 7th-6th centuries BCE to 3rd-5th centuries CE"}
skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "a42df896-45ba-4800-bd8a-f6e4a651225d", "value": "Sargat culture (forest-steppe of the Western Siberia and Trans-Urals)"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "04a84de3-5bfa-4844-9acb-89fc0dd073ec", "value": "?From the arrival of Islam, c. 650CE to the end of the Timurid dynasty 1507 CE"}
{"id": "f3a5d933-9c84-4c6f-98f6-50b0c2055f56", "value": "Examination, recording and plotting of variations in the electrical resistivity of soils in order to locate and define buried features."}

{"id": "87bda932-1122-41f3-be5b-4bc8da5354f0", "value": "Technique using electromagnetic fields to map subsurface electrical conductivity anomalies. Can be used as a high-sensitivity metal detector."}

{"id": "1aad9bb6-eaa8-4e7d-87ae-45852db4439f", "value": "A geophysical technique for imaging subsurface structures in cross section from electrical measurements made at the surface, or by electrodes in one or more boreholes."}

{"id": "e5cf2b72-52ba-4378-93d6-160ba0903c54", "value": "A limited programme of intrusive fieldwork which determines the presence or absence of archaeological features, structures, deposits, artefacts or ecofacts within a specified underwater area."}
{"id": "3ec3da8f-25b8-41d8-b7b5-708e3e80fc6c", "value": "The taking of photographs from above using photographic equipment mounted on, or used from an aircraft or other airborne vehicle."}

{"id": "756050b0-083a-44db-8c28-7fa1dac5d2aa", "value": "The interpretation of information on aerial photographs usually resulting in the production of maps and records of archaeological sites and landscapes. Many aerial photographs may be consulted for a single analytical survey."}

{"id": "5bbe4bcc-8150-427e-8de9-c0b68c7374d9", "value": "Capturing visible spectrum photographs or images of monument features or character using still or motion cameras from an aircraft or other airborne vehicle or apparatus. Covers both digital and film-based cameras."}

{"id": "8450fcca-e848-4113-9680-a582b8f1fb4c", "value": "Recording using specialist equipment that allows discrete wavelengths in the visible spectrum and beyond to be recorded. The combination of different spectral bands allows features to be identified that would not be visible to the naked eye."}

{"id": "13851dae-1f86-4142-bf84-5ea282d97f7f", "value": "Northwestern Kyrgyzstan, valley of the Talas River valley, between two mountain ranges. \u00d6tm\u00f6k Pass into the Suusamyr Valley and the T\u00f6\u00f6 Ashuu Pass before descending to the Chuy Valley."}
{"id": "013032a5-e3cd-4298-850b-11d9e2a94fee", "value": "Human activity in Central Asia from c. 50,000 to 40,000 BP to c. 6th/5th millennia BCE. c. 1,500,000-16,000 BP"}

{"id": "8f87444d-9fb4-422f-9e2d-c71bf92e861a", "value": "Systematic recording of building facades that produces a seamless mosaic of digital images by identifying control points and defining limits to each image. The rectified mosaic can then be introduced into a CAD environment."}

{"id": "fd0300be-e19d-4b23-bf51-3ef9c22aab02", "value": "The measurement of a surface, either in elevation or plan, determined from measurements derived from two or more photographic images taken from different positions; this allows three dimensional viewing of the surface to be mapped."}

{"id": "b09c6888-6cd2-4e77-a3cc-166b869fca9d", "value": "A field and desk based assessment of heritage asset condition and vulnerability so that informed decisions can be made regarding how best to manage the resource."}

{"id": "306d4b82-f7ad-4567-b792-a671a206745f", "value": "A site visit to ascertain the nature and extent of the site and its surrounding environs by means of a visual inspection from which a written and/or photographic record is made."}

{"id": "bb2ad067-57c8-430d-91cb-cf5f4ba01a53", "value": "An information gathering exercise to facilitate an understanding of the potential environmental impact of a development proposal; includes the collation of specialist reports from a variety of disciplines."}

{"id": "2baa3981-7d6e-4eac-9414-3635d3b2bd46", "value": "A programme of assessment of the known or potential archaeological resource within a specified area or site on land, inter-tidal zone or underwater by the consultation and collation of existing written, graphic, photographic and electronic data."}
{"id": "9a467ff9-0297-49e1-beea-20dab3a42a35", "value": "Observations made by an archaeologist or architectural historian as the result of a field visit to a site or monument."}

{"id": "fbc64f19-ac17-408c-82e4-2311a8632188", "value": "An holistic approach to landscape, using GIS, which maps diversity of landscape character as a means to managing future change in ways that are appropriate and sustainable."}

{"id": "787f39c9-4a1a-4b08-a7b2-26ae983e9caf", "value": "An overview of the historical and architectural development, character and heritage assets of a settlement or area. An HAA may result in the creation, at varying levels of intensity, of individual site-based records informed by area context."}

{"id": "23b19c20-c56b-40ac-9136-ed0e3e21faab", "value": "Observations made by antiquarians (Those who studied sites and landscapes prior to archaeology and architectural history becoming established disciplines in the 19th century) and reported through publication or from unpublished manuscripts."}
{"id": "fb3236e4-a029-45c9-a40a-8dab3fdbaf03", "value": "Programmes of research that seek to identify the archaeological and/or architectural significance of a site or landscape."}

{"id": "8a887bd9-45ab-4a78-8bc4-374ecfc613dd", "value": "The supposed detection of subsurface features by employing a twig, copper rod, pendulum, or other instrument. Discontinuous movements in these instruments are believed by some to record the existence of buried features."}

{"id": "70f83617-3693-4617-a749-f18a904f6f0e", "value": "Detailed survey using photographic images to record archaeological and architectural sites or features of interest. Record photography is an important aspect of recording such features before they are destroyed."}

{"id": "a8b94700-ed9a-42a7-a056-e5d491fffbd5", "value": "A limited programme of intrusive fieldwork which determines the presence or absence of archaeological features, structures, deposits, artefacts or ecofacts within a specified area or site on land or within the inter-tidal zone."}
{"id": "aa7d96ab-c570-4729-81ef-3cde999dbf44", "value": "Systematically positioned hole, or holes, utilised in all studies that aim to sample the nature of the topsoil and subsurface deposits."}

{"id": "cacafbb8-610d-48c4-b7a3-de700a1e8f08", "value": "Archaeologically excavated trench, either hand of machine dug, as part of a sampling programme to evaluate the presence/absence, nature, preservation, age and extent of any buried archaeological features."}

{"id": "d9aec342-483c-4b7b-bb46-a845e317a9b5", "value": "A sensing technique that consists of measuring minute variations in the gravitational pull of the Earth in order to detect gravity anomalies arising from voids and cavities within the earth."}

{"id": "5f3e57f9-8a6f-4507-94fa-3102b536728e", "value": "Type of survey involving the drilling of deep and narrow shafts in the ground used to describe deposits, understand stratigraphy and collect cores amples."}
{"id": "f6048009-820e-45d7-aa36-1ecf0cfbe49d", "value": "Transect or area-based arrangements of drilled auger-holes used to describe deposits and collect samples."}
{"id": "f460a455-943d-4eeb-8404-acbd0ec8d6dd", "value": "The retrieval of samples for laboratory analysis from buried features that have been sampled using boring equipment."}

{"id": "6c71c7c1-49b4-436a-9267-fdca808396f3", "value": "Konstantin Salnikov (1967) divided the Andronovo Culture into three stages: Fedorovo (18 - 16 centuries BCE), Alakul (15 - 12 centuries BCE) and Zamaraev (12 - 8 centuries BCE). Some would place start closer to 2000 BCE. Debate over date range continue. c. 2,000-900 BCE."}
{"id": "54f899fe-f4c0-45c6-b929-6d1242cade58", "value": "c. 2,000-1600 BCE. Some see as precursor to Andronova culture."}

{"id": "fe8f5200-54c5-41e6-aca1-d26b9657430a", "value": "Periodic visits being made to a site by an archaeologist to record archaeological deposits and recover finds that have come to light since the previous visit. An archaeological presence is not maintained during groundwork as it is with a watching brief."}

{"id": "4a6dd085-b690-45e0-99c9-5daea86d9e2d", "value": "A formal programme of observation and investigation conducted during any operation carried out for non-archaeological reasons that may damage archaeological deposits. This will be within a specified area or site on land, inter-tidal zone or underwater."}

{"id": "3ae3188a-2c78-4004-9945-640e88ae27b5", "value": "The monitoring of the excavation of a hole made by a non-archaeologically trained person. Any archaeological evidence that comes to light is recorded by the archaeologist during the course of the work although he/she cannot suspend the groundwork."}
{"id": "736ca4ec-0c4c-4d2c-a430-c0fff2e3ed1a", "value": "The extraction of a limited quantity of wood for scientific analysis."}

{"id": "b174ff36-fe04-4a66-918c-9011f155161c", "value": "The extraction of wood samples for dating analysis. Tree ring dating is the science of dating cultural and environmental events in the past by comparative study of the growth rings in trees and aged wood."}
{"id": "9fa25b29-7227-47fd-9ed8-108876182b03", "value": "This concept contains the countries that are contained in the CAAL database"}

{"id": "691dc3f8-018e-4a61-8773-03ed523ee0da", "value": "The controlled measurement of natural and artificial landscape features to produce a measured plan or a 3D data set reading as a plan. Features are depicted by either hachures, symbols or contour lines."}

{"id": "c851c306-0ce5-4459-8b1f-ee088a7e1e94", "value": "The accurate survey and analytical depiction of earthworks and their relative chronological relationships by means of hachures and related symbols."}

{"id": "1f82ae9b-3d66-459d-961e-3683b4e8235d", "value": "The non intrusive processes by which information is collected about the location, distribution and organisation of past human activities. The approaches can be either extensive or intensive depending the objectivies that need to be addressed."}

{"id": "8bafb457-5d94-4659-93c8-f352bcceda6f", "value": "The investigation of heritage assets along thematic lines, usually to inform the production of a thematic study. Such studies bring specialist insights to bear on the particular area of study, but may not address other aspects of the site's significance."}
{"id": "f175d981-9007-4ed1-92b6-f6e775dc96e4", "value": "A dimensional check on a building or site giving detailed measurements."}

{"id": "7b41232e-51a2-404f-bc22-67f67bb6d856", "value": "Field survey undertaken to investigate land formation processes often carried out in association with, or in the vicinity of, an archaeological site, or as part of a wider landscape project."}
{"id": "4318f29e-72b4-4f42-9c12-f8309a97b21a", "value": "The recording of a surface, or surfaces, using scanning technologies, to create a 3D model of the target structure/object."}

{"id": "d09d44f7-3567-436e-9edd-252c85dc310a", "value": "Structured and carefully executed scanning of the ground surface with a metal detecting device in order to recover surface scatters of metal objects and plot them spatially within the study area; a technique useful in battlefield archaeology."}

{"id": "6ab47d02-d331-41fc-a2b7-205acf17fafb", "value": "The taking of photographs during informal site visits, which may be undertaken by amateur archaeologists or architectural students. More formal, detailed surveys should be termed Photographic Survey."}

{"id": "ff63367c-1424-4de2-8ca3-da94d2869410", "value": "A descriptive survey involving the systematic measurement and recording of the dimensions or features of a building. Where the survey is accompanied by systematic investigation and analysis, use Architectural Survey."}

{"id": "00576956-afef-44d4-ae74-35fe3b61534d", "value": "The non intrusive processes by which information is collected about the location, distribution and organisation of past human activities that are now submerged by water. The approaches can be either extensive or intensive depending on the objectives."}

{"id": "a44f4bf6-6a03-48b2-bb4f-56fb1a202579", "value": "Recording and analysis of built structures utilising close observation as well as manual or electronic survey equipment such as GPS and REDM (Reflectorless Electromagnetic Distance Measurement). Includes research, fieldwork and a report."}

{"id": "7dd86d0a-94b4-4ee2-9fec-e8c06e346229", "value": "A planned programme of investigation conducted within a defined area aimed at identifying and surveying previously unrecorded sites and checking the condition of known sites."}

{"id": "67fa9219-2d78-4623-9820-0621c0b6305d", "value": "Ground-based or marine subsurface mapping of archaeological features using different sensing technologies. Most commonly applied are magnetometers, electrical resistance meters, ground penetrating radar, side scan sonar, and electromagnetic conductivity."}
{"id": "52e7cf70-0e70-4467-864c-3fa600624942", "value": "A subsurface detection method performed by striking the ground with a heavy wooden mallet or a lead-filled container on a long handle."}

{"id": "052205fd-7e30-4604-98df-d6a01f63ef90", "value": "The assessment of the age of a hedge based on its nature, condition and the number and type of woody plant species present. Most surveys make use of Hooper's hypothesis which states that for every 27m a new woody species invades a hedge every 100 years."}
{"id": "11b1cb00-d3ce-43cf-ab34-92152f904694", "value": "Turkic dynasty (999\u20131211 CE) that ruled in Transoxania in Central Asia. Also spelled Karakhanid"}

{"id": "65c91fab-5e02-49fa-bc0a-763da1eb5932", "value": "A maritime technique similar in theory to sub bottom profilers, however for 3D seismic surveys the receiver array is more complex involving multiple receivers so that a volume of sediment is studied rather than a single 2D line."}

{"id": "6dffb761-94d2-43bc-bd5e-8d8b90d64147", "value": "The Eastern Turkic Khaganate was formed at the beginning of the 7th century (593\u2013603 CE) after the split of the G\u00f6kt\u00fcrk Khaganate. Subjugated by the Tang Empire in 630 CE."}

{"id": "1b35bc65-b856-40a7-b8e4-2b056a6d4f71", "value": "An extra processing unit which can be used in conjunction with single beam echo sounders to determine the roughness and hardness of the seafloor. Mainly used for marine biology, but has been used in archaeology."}

{"id": "113c16ff-296c-4edf-bb37-97374fb18ddd", "value": "An investigative method using an infrared camera to detect temperature differences in the ground. The thermal camera does not record the actual temperature of the object in question. Instead the camera records the infrared radiation emitted by the object."}

{"id": "62215a04-0eb6-4ede-a3d2-e87603ea23de", "value": "A specific type of Infrared photography that uses an airborne scanning infrared sensor to record differential spectrums of features both extant and buried."}

{"id": "49858fcc-364d-4557-95b7-fc6bc63cb530", "value": "Terminology used for recording archaeological and architectural investigative, data collection exercises; from intrusive interventions to non damaging surveys"}
{"id": "281c87ae-e774-41a7-a101-a462ab0caef4", "value": "The content types are part of the Archive record"}

{"id": "718bc155-dfd3-457d-b722-b04ea130ab42", "value": "A system of excavation, developed by Mortimer Wheeler, whereby a site was uncovered by means of a grid of square trenches with baulks between them to aid the recording of the stratification of all four sides of each trench."}

{"id": "a9dc9265-31a9-4b3d-9fea-786b5d8c5142", "value": "The taking of samples at regular intervals from the surface of a study area in order to retrieve information on the different chemical elements present."}

{"id": "575d0820-9aa5-43dd-b726-cf65d61ac1ef", "value": "Bactria\u2013Margiana Archaeological Complex, a Bronze Age civilization of Central Asia, dated to c. 2400-1600 BCE, located in present-day northern Afghanistan, eastern Turkmenistan, southern Uzbekistan and western Tajikistan."}

{"id": "0c390ad1-7910-42c9-a308-5e7e6c9a7da1", "value": "Controlled investigation, recording and removal of archaeological deposits according to the principles of strategraphic excavation. The size of an open area can range from holes to examine pile foundations to extensive trenches of 100 square meters."}
{"id": "a935562a-4a8a-4aaa-897d-a1f4ac255e90", "value": "The title types are part of the Archive record"}

{"id": "91c97905-168d-419d-8b40-52d83477521d", "value": "Light detection and ranging is a type of aircraft based remote sensing which records reflected laser pulses. The data can be used to produce very accurate digital elevation models. For ground-based work use LASER SCANNING SURVEY."}
{"id": "867e9158-4e87-436f-9f23-78493f294ab9", "value": "The use of a metal detector to locate metal artefacts on an archaeological excavation that otherwise would go unnoticed. "}

{"id": "49bc0edd-6156-4fdf-93db-7e00483dbb45", "value": "Controlled investigation, recording and removal of archaeological deposits in targeted areas in order to answer specific questions relating to a particular archaeological site or landscape. Usually undertaken by university departments or amateur groups."}
{"id": "7fc614eb-0fb3-4d0a-8154-9d2c7ea011a9", "value": "?From the arrival of Islam, c. 650CE to the start of the Seljuk era, 1037CE"}
{"id": "54429988-0da9-41c0-9721-13b70087479e", "value": "From the Islamic conquest to c 11th century CE"}

{"id": "d0e4af94-123c-4872-b528-8b8cdd4e9aa2", "value": "Controlled intrusive fieldwork which examines, records and interprets archaeological deposits, features and structures and, as appropriate, retrieves artefacts and ecofact remains within a specified underwater area."}

{"id": "f2223719-4f04-4c2d-be1d-667501dc66cc", "value": "Aerial photography using infrared sensitive film or sensors to reveal soil and vegetation characteristics not apparent in photographs derived from conventional aerial photography."}

{"id": "2aee5d0f-fb26-407e-a398-67cfc38aefe7", "value": "Controlled investigation, recording and removal of archaeological deposits under threat of destruction from building development. A pre PPG 16 activity, usually under strict time constraints."}

{"id": "7e717705-cd74-4903-9edc-30cb590a73bf", "value": "Removal of a sample from a vertical section generally using a U sectioned tin to extract an intact column of the observed stratigraphy. Used in the study of pollen, diatoms etc."}

{"id": "c625c810-83b6-461d-aa7e-f3d95034ba7a", "value": "Removal of samples from deposits, including archaeological contexts to recover information about past environments and economies, retrieve material for scientific dating and for the investigation of the deposits themselves e.g. formation processes."}

{"id": "dd9de47e-61a9-4bb6-8a19-2ac680d855f7", "value": "An excavation technique that involves the machine stripping the topsoil/subsoil from the area to be excavated, plotting observed features onto a site plan and then partially or fully excavating those features."}

{"id": "1b9ae903-c4b1-45f0-9407-ce4c33107a96", "value": "A maritime coring technique which uses vibration to facilitate ground penetration. With the force of gravity, and sometimes a piston, it can penetrate much deeper layers although the vibration provokes a slight mixing of the sediments."}

{"id": "6afd44bf-455e-4c48-b337-d07cb0999cb0", "value": "An acoustic method which involves the creation of a shock wave through the ground. By recording the time interval between the initial shock and the reflected or refracted shock waves it is possible to define subsurface deposits."}

{"id": "7432e8b4-ce27-4d81-ae31-e6e122c93f99", "value": "Airborne survey to discover, record and monitor archaeological sites and other heritage assets. Sites will usually be recorded by aerial photography."}

{"id": "6d85ae11-e1cf-4fb7-9d50-fe9886a5d163", "value": "A maritime coring technique which penetrates the ground due to the force of gravity. Since the speed of penetration is the same as the sampling speed, it barely disrupts the sedimentary layers. A cable attached to the ship is used to recover the core."}

{"id": "f7c368c6-83c4-4f99-88d6-6146397efd9a", "value": "The capture of imagery using an orbiting satellite. The type of imagery is very varied including visible light photography, infrared and multi spectral photography as well as imagery derived from radar and lidar data."}

{"id": "297c83be-7c55-4e94-b55c-6a85b8daf6d7", "value": "The extraction of samples from selected features on a site to identify a characteristic magnetic response from sediments derived from the features in order to predict the response that similar features would produce. Also used to prospect for sites."}

{"id": "481bf167-7c44-47f0-95e5-8c563fc1bbe3", "value": "Survey using a magnetometer, a device capable of detecting variations in magnetic susceptibility between topsoils, subsoils and rocks, can also be used in a maritime context to detect variations in the magnetic field of seabed sediments."}

{"id": "b1a15acc-84ae-42fd-8439-72865ed947ce", "value": "The Samanid Empire, also known as the Samanian Empire, Samanid dynasty, Samanid Emirate, or simply Samanids, ruled from 819 to 999 CE. The empire was centred in Khorasan and Transoxiana."}

{"id": "703be6d5-863d-4da2-a2b7-09dedf281b4c", "value": "A technique utilised in maritime recording; a remote operated vehicle (ROV) is a tethered underwater robot. ROVs have been used to locate and inspect a number of historic shipwrecks in depths beyond the reach of human divers."}

{"id": "f0db482c-0cda-4440-84f1-a3e6d1f05bfc", "value": "Test pits dug by geotechnical engineers or engineering geologists to obtain information on the physical properties of soil, sediments and bedrock around a site to design earthworks and foundations for proposed structures."}

{"id": "bce1bdd3-ecc1-428b-8264-185886583b46", "value": "A technique that measures the amount of time it takes pulses of electromagnetic energy sent into the ground, from a transmitter, to reflect back from the interfaces between layers and other subsurface features in order to produce a subsurface profile."}
{"id": "2464a712-22a1-4f89-a133-0f774514a80e", "value": " Turkic dynasty (999\u20131211 CE) that ruled in Transoxania in Central Asia. Also spelled Qarakhanids"}

{"id": "5727620f-049f-4abf-90fb-df4a9198483d", "value": "The Western Turkic Khaganate (or Onoq Khaganate) was a Turkic khaganate formed beginning of the 7th century (593\u2013603 CE) after the split of the G\u00f6kt\u00fcrk Khaganate. Subjugated by the Tang Empire in 657 CE."}

{"id": "0dcdb095-504e-48fb-97b3-d8ff03c4336a", "value": "Survey using photographic or other recording equipment mounted on or used from either an aircraft or other airborne vehicle or a maritime vessel/submersible craft."}

{"id": "44e85e80-6cb9-46fc-968b-a2c2f9f6d618", "value": "Controlled intrusive fieldwork which examines, records and interprets archaeological deposits, features and structures and, as appropriate, retrieves artefacts and ecofact remains within a specified area or site on land or within the inter-tidal zone."}
